What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Math 115 was really hard. Regardless of what instructor you get, the material is very difficult and the pace is really fast. I wouldn't recommend the class unless you have to take it to fulfill major requirements.
Yes but I would warn them about the considerable self-study portion of the syllabus. The subject matter seemed fairly dry but is necessary for further studies in Math.
I mean, I'd recommend it because it's useful. But, it was my least favorite class overall because I would do fine on homework, and be dumbstruck on tests.
The tests require an extremely conceptual knowledge of the material along with practical.

I would recommend math 115 to fellow students but this course is not by any means "easy" even if you have taken a comparable high school course. Tests are based on the concepts you learn and sometimes combine several concepts so tests can seem a little abstract. Some weeks problems sets are easy while others they are challenging. The course is manageable and I do not regret taking it.

Math 115 was frustrating in the sense that it was focused more upon turning in psets and taking an exam than really understanding the material. I would only recommend the course because it is a necessary class on the math track, not for the quality of the course.
